What is a server ?

A server is a computer device that provides a service to another computer program and its user, also known as the client.

What is the role of the domain name ?
The role of a domain name is to help users identify internet resources.

What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com ?
The DNS record type for www.footbar.com is A type

What is the role of the web server ?
The role of a web server is to process and manage HTTP/HTTPS requests and response.

What is the role of the application server ?
The role of the application server is to store and run an application for client computers.

What is the role of the database ?
The role of a database is to organize information for easy accessibility.

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website ?
Servers use HyperText Transfer Protocol (HTTP) to communicate with web browsers.

Issues with this infrastructure:
Single Point of Failure (SPOF): If for instance the server fails, being that its a single server, users will be interrupted. In terms of downtime, if there is any maintenance on the web application, the service will be interrupted. This is because there is only one server in this infrastructure. It cannnot scale, it is designed for minimal usage, by a few users. 

